alert.note: Alert for Carver; Scott; Sibley (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 22 at 11:27AM CDT until May 25 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Scott, Carver, Hennepin and Dakota Counties. Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties. Minnesota River at Henderson MN19 affecting Scott, Sibley and Le Sueur Counties. ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota and Wisconsin... Mississippi River near Hastings L/D 2 (COE) affecting Washington, Pierce, Dakota and Goodhue Counties. Mississippi River at St. Paul affecting Washington, Ramsey and Dakota Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL THURSDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River near Jordan. * WHEN...Until Thursday evening. * IMPACTS...At 26.7 feet, The bridge at Scott County Road 9 and Carver County Road 11/Jonathan Carver Parkway will be closed. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1045 AM CDT Monday, the stage was 27.3 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 1045 AM CDT Monday was 27.5 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage early Thursday morning and continue falling to 21.1 feet Monday morning. - Flood stage is 25.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 27.2 feet on 05/13/1993. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas.
